OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FRon Hope: Met Police's     
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Ffirst black police         
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Finspector dies aged 68     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Ronald Hope, the first black person to 
OL,6, be made an inspector in the            
OL,7, Metropolitan Police, has died aged 68. 
OL,9,FMr Hope was a founding member and the  
OL,10,Ffirst elected chair of the Met Black   
OL,11,FPolice Association (MBPA).             
OL,13,FHe was born in south London to a       
OL,14,FGuyanese father and an English mother, 
OL,15,Fand joined the police in1973, staying  
OL,16,Fwith the force for the next 30 years.  
OL,18,FAfter retirement from the Met he worked
OL,19,Fin anti-corruption, focussing on       
OL,20,Fmatch-fixing in international cricket. 
